
## Fill Box Procedures

The following instructions explain the procedure for filling an empty box:



1. Use forklift to move empty box onto rail system in front of the fill box. 
2. Safely dismount forklift, push in empty fill box **(see Fig. 4)**, and shut tarp.
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 4 Pushing In Empty Fill Box.png" alt="Fig 4" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 4:** Pushing In Empty Fill Box*
<br>

3. Tarp off fill station on both sides and secure tarp with magnetic mounts **(see Fig. 5 & Fig. 6).**
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 5 Tarping Off Fill Station.png" alt="Fig 5" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 5:** Tarping Off Fill Station*
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 6 Securing Fill Station Tarp with Magnetic Mounts.png" alt="Fig 6" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 6:** Securing Fill Station Tarp with Magnetic Mounts*
<br>

4. Ensure CMAXX is on and running **(see Facility Opening Procedures on pg. XX  if needed)**.
   
5. Ensure Auger lever is in the **ON** position and press the **START** button **(see Fig. 7)**.
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 7 On Switch for Auger.png" alt="Fig 7" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 7:** On Switch for Auger*
<br>

6. Monitor the fill status of the fill box closely to ensure that box does not overflow. Rake the fill pile down into a flat pile with a shovel** (see Fig. 8)**. Ensure even distribution. 
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 8 Raking Down Pile.jpg" alt="Fig 8" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 8:** Raking Down Pile*
<br>

7. Turn on the Hopper vibrator as needed to maintain Auger flow. Typically, vibration adjuster should be set around **7**. **(see Fig. 9)**. 
<br>
    <img src="20_Media\Figure 9 Hopper Vibrator Control.png" alt="Fig 9" style="margin-left: 0em;"/><br> ***Figure 9:** Hopper Vibrator Control*
<br>

8. Assess which shape is being printed and fill box to  appropriate level. 

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;**Wave Brush:** 2500 lbs - 3000 lbs


&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;**Wave Slope:** 4000 lbs - 4200 lbs


&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;**Fish House:** 4000 lbs - 4200 lbs


&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;**Lattice:** 4000 lbs - 4200 lbs
<br>

9. Once box is filled to appropriate level, follow step A, B, or C accordingly: 

    &nbsp;
        A.)  If current print is in process and print staging area is occupied, allow print process to complete. Pull newly filled box backwards and fork it to the box yard for later retrieval. <br>
        B.) If a print is complete and print staging area is unoccupied, but the new box is still filling, check box-yard for a full box and fork this box to the print staging area. <br>
        C.) If a print is complete, the print staging area is unoccupied, and the new box has completed filling, manually push the box through to the print staging area.